title: Serialize/Attribute-normalized
description: AST-only mode drops whitespace around the attribute equals sign
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

`p = blah` becomes `p="blah"`: the whitespace around the equals sign is
dropped and bare values are quoted.

Why: the AST records attribute name and value only, so tree-only
serialization emits the canonical form.

* Covers: serializeAttribute's canonical fallback in $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/utils/parsetree.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

<div p = blah>some text</div>
+
title: ExpectedWikitext

<div p="blah">some text</div>
